[[File:Louis Caravaque, Portrait of Empress Anna Ioannovna (1730).jpg|thumb|right|200px|Portrait of Empress Anna Ioannovna, 1730. Now at the [[Tretyakov Gallery]], Moscow.]]
'''Louis Caravaque''', a French [[portrait]] painter, was a native of [[Gascony]]. He went to Russia, and in 1716 painted at [[Astrakhan]] the portrait of [[Peter the Great]], which has been engraved by Massard and by [[Eustache-Hyacinthe Langlois|Langlois]]. He again painted the [[Tsar|Czar]] in 1723, and subsequently the Empresses [[Anna of Russia|Anne]] and [[Elizabeth of Russia|Elizabeth]]. He died in Russia in 1752. 

